  <description><![CDATA[<p>The Grand Hotel Diana Majestic is a great base if you want to explore <a data-udi="umb://document/c0a1a2eb5f21493d858ec9013916a8fb" href="/{localLink:umb://document/c0a1a2eb5f21493d858ec9013916a8fb}" title="Liguria">Liguria</a>. It’s in <a data-udi="umb://document/b5972678189a4aaebae6a188ea567f1f" href="/{localLink:umb://document/b5972678189a4aaebae6a188ea567f1f}" title="Diano Marina">Diano Marina</a>, a lovely seaside town that’s on the west cost of the Italian Riviera. The train station in the town makes it easy to explore the coastline – head to the neighbouring towns of Sanremo and Alassio or go further afield and visit the French Riviera too. The train runs along the coastline with fantastic views for almost the whole journey.</p>
<p>The hotel’s located right on the coast and it’s got a private sandy beach. The beaches in Liguria are some of the best in <a data-udi="umb://document/a1a80922d88a43f8ba80b182c72e8904" href="/{localLink:umb://document/a1a80922d88a43f8ba80b182c72e8904}" title="Italy">Italy</a> so make sure you take some time to relax here and enjoy the clean sea water. There’s two outdoor pools and lovely gardens too so there’s no shortage of places to relax. Spend the whole day here and grab some lunch at the poolside restaurant. There’s three further restaurants that open for dinner. The Terrace Restaurant is included on half board and is great for trying out lots of local flavours, with four courses every night. If you want to upgrade one evening, we can recommend trying the gourmet seafood restaurant. The centre of Diano Marina is about a kilometre away so it’s easy to walk into town for a nightcap.</p>
<p>Transfer time: approx. 1 hour 30 mins from Genoa or Nice. Private transfers included.</p>]]></description>
